String:
Immutable - cannot able to manipulate(in-string). will create another copy(manipulated) in new address, if we try to re-assign.

Takes more memory

less efficient for string manipulation 


String-Buffer:
Mutable 

It does not  create another copy(manipulated) in new address. instead all the opeartions takes place in the same string.

Takes less memory

More efficient than string class for  manipulation 
